17.body:
fn main() { pub struct Animal { pub name: String, legs: u32, pub(crate) wings: u32, } pub struct Dog { pub name: String, legs: u32, } pub enum AnimalTypes { Chicken(Animal, u32), Dog(Dog), Other(String), BadTypesystemUse((String, String, u32, String, String)), } let list = vec![ AnimalTypes::Chicken( Animal { name: "Chicken".to_string(), legs: 2, wings: 2, }, 5, ), AnimalTypes::Chicken( Animal { name: "Chicken".to_string(), legs: 2, wings: 2, }, 3, ), AnimalTypes::Dog(Dog { name: "Dog".to_string(), legs: 4, }), AnimalTypes::Other("Other".to_string()), ]; let res = list.iter().fold(0u32, |acc, x| match x { AnimalTypes::Chicken(.., count) => *count + acc, AnimalTypes::Dog(_) => acc, AnimalTypes::Other(_) => acc, AnimalTypes::BadTypesystemUse(_) => { panic!("Bad typesystem use") } } ); println!("res: {}", res); let legs = list.iter().fold(0u32, |acc, x| match x { AnimalTypes::Chicken(Animal{ legs, ..}, ..) => *legs + acc, AnimalTypes::Dog(Dog { legs, ..}) => *legs + acc, AnimalTypes::Other(_) => acc, AnimalTypes::BadTypesystemUse(_) => { panic!("Bad typesystem use") } } ); println!("legs: {}", legs);
}

18.body: Use clone,ref,as_ref to silence the borrow checker Avoid Box, Cell, RefCell, Arc, Mutex, etc Avoid Generics in the beginning Avoid writing your own macros Aim for understanding async and multithreading, channels soon (very valuable) -> Next Session Now you need Arc and maybe Mutex Build a small real application (cli tool, website, Client App) Forget about OOD. Rust is all about procedural programming with a strong typesystem. https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch17-00-oop.html

9.body: fn main() { let text = String::from("Hello World"); let print = |text: String| { println!("{text}")}; print(text); //println!("{text}"); Compile error } fn main() { let text = String::from("Hello World"); let print = move || { println!("{text}")}; print(); // println!("{text}"); } fn main() { let text = String::from("Hello World"); let print = || { println!("{text}")}; print(); println!("{text}"); } fn main() { let mut text = String::from("Hello World"); let mut mutate = || { text = String::from("Hi"); }; mutate(); println!("{text}"); } fn main() { let mut text = String::from("Hello World"); let mut mutate = move || { text = String::from("Hi"); text }; let text = mutate(); println!("{text}"); } fn main() { let text = String::from("Hello World"); let print = |text: &String| { println!("{text}"); let mut t = text.to_owned(); t+="++"; println!("{t}"); }; print(&text); println!("{text}"); }
